\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. C. glaber} L., {\i Mantissa Alt. }179 (1771) ({\i Pycreus glaber} (L.) Hayek). Caespitose annual; stems 8-50 cm. Leaves 2-6 mm wide, shorter than to exceeding the stems. Bracts 2-5, exceeding the inflorescence. Inflorescence a simple umbel of dense heads; rays up to 8, up to 6 cm. Spikelets 6-15 × 2 mm, linear or oblong-lanceolate, with 10-24 flowers, patent. Rhachilla narrowly winged. Glumes 2-2·5 × c. 1·5 mm, elliptical or ovate, acute, reddish, straw-coloured or brownish, with a wide greenish centre and a narrow hyaline margin. Stamens (2)3. Nut 1/2-3/5 as long as the glumes, obovoid, brown or blackish.{\i  C. & S.E. Europe.} Au Bu Gr It Ju Rm Rs (W, K, E) Si Tu.
