\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. C. textilis} Thunb.,{\i  Prodr. Pl. Cap.} 18 (1794). Caespitose, leafless perennial; rhizomes short, thick, woody; stems 60-90 cm. Bracts 8-12, with revolute margins, exceeding the inflorescence. Inflorescence a compound umbel of rather dense heads; rays 8-12, up to 6 cm. Spikelets 6-8 × 1·5-2 mm, lanceolate, with 8-20 flowers, patent. Rhachilla not winged. Glumes 1·5-2 × c. 1 mm, ovate, acute, with a mucro c. 0·1 mm, pale yellow or brown, often with a greenish centre. Stamens 3. Nut c. ½ as long as the glumes, brown.{\i  Naturalized in Açores }({\i Sao Miguel}). [Az.] ({\i S. Africa}.)
